query": "You are an expert Python programmer. You will be given a question (problem specification) and will generate a correct Python program that matches the specification and passes all tests.\n\n### Question:\nGiven an array of integers nums and an integer k, return the number of unique k-diff pairs in the array.\nA k-diff pair is an integer pair (nums[i], nums[j]), where the following are true:\n\n0 <= i, j < nums.length\ni != j\n|nums[i] - nums[j]| == k\n\nNotice that |val| denotes the absolute value of val.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: nums = [3,1,4,1,5], k = 2\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: There are two 2-diff pairs in the array, (1, 3) and (3, 5).\nAlthough we have two 1s in the input, we should only return the number of unique pairs.\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: nums = [1,2,3,4,5], k = 1\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: There are four 1-diff pairs in the array, (1, 2), (2, 3), (3, 4) and (4, 5).\n\nExample 3:\n\nInput: nums = [1,3,1,5,4], k = 0\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: There is one 0-diff pair in the array, (1, 1).\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 104\n-107 <= nums[i] <= 107\n0 <= k <= 107\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def findPairs(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def findPairs(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        if k < 0:\n            return 0\n        \n        num_counts = {}\n        for num in nums:\n            num_counts[num] = num_counts.get(num, 0) + 1\n        \n        count = 0\n        for num in num_counts:\n            if k == 0:\n                if num_counts[num] > 1:\n                    count += 1\n            else:\n                if num + k in num_counts:\n                    count += 1\n        \n        return count\n```\n\nThis solution uses a dictionary to count the occurrences of each number in the array. It then iterates through the unique numbers and checks for the existence of the required pair based on the value of `k`. If `k` is 0, it checks if any number appears more than once. If `k` is greater than 0, it checks if the number plus `k` exists in the dictionary. This approach ensures that only unique pairs are counted.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}